Version Control

1. Version Control System
2. Centralised Version Control System
3. Distributed Version Control System

Git commands

git --version (for checking the git versions)

SET UP THE CONFIGURATION FOR GIT
git config --global --list
git config --global user.name "name"
git config --global user.email "emaid-id"

Working Directory -> Staging Area

git status -> to track the changes of files
git init -> to initialise the git repository

git init -b main (by default we get master to this will give main)

TO ADD TO STAGING AREA
git add "filename"

TO CHECK THE LOG AREA
git log

git commit -m "Commit Message"
git diff -> to check the difference between files

git rm --cached creds.txt


GITHUB, GITLAB, BITBUCKED

INTEGRATION WITH GITHUB

git clone "repository_link"
git branch -M main
ssh-keygen -o (generating public and private key)
.ssh -> cat id_rsa.pub
 
 Github -> Settings -> SSH -> New SSH Key -> Add title and key
 
 git remote add origin ssh_link
 git push -u origin main
 git tag v1.1 -m "27th June release"
 git tag
 git push origin v1.0
 
 git log --pretty=oneline
 
 GIT BRANCH
 git branch --all
 git branch
 git branch -d branch_name (delete the branch)
 
